The paper deals with image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and medical imaging. The use of neural networks for registration is a recent trend in the field of computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to registration using recurrent neural networks, which involves learning a sequence of local deformations to achieve the desired registration accuracy. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for registration also involves optimization and numerical methods, which may make the paper relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
